  {
    "problem_id": "op_python_script_1",
    "problem_text": "What number will be printed while executing the following Python 3 script?\n\n```python\ndef calculate_value():\n    x = 7\n    y = 3\n    z = 0\n    for i in range(1, 21):\n        if x % 2 == 0:\n            x = (x // 2) + y\n            y = y + 1\n        else:\n            x = (x * 3) + 1 - y\n            y = y - 2\n        \n        if y < 0:\n            y = y + i\n            \n        z += x - y\n        \n    return z\n\nprint(calculate_value())\n```",
    "ground_truth": "517949",
    "source": "original_problems_4_10_26",
    "topic": "code_tracing"
  },
  {
    "problem_id": "op_python_script_2",
    "problem_text": "What number will be printed while executing the following Python 3 script?\n\n```python\nimport re\n\ndef analyze_logs():\n    log_data = \"\"\"[SYS] temp=45C fan=1200rpm status=OK\n    [USR] temp=35C fan=800rpm status=OK\n    [SYS] temp=105C fan=3000rpm status=WARN\n    [SYS] temp=50C fan=0rpm status=ERR\n    [SYS] temp=12C fan=1500rpm status=OK\n    [sys] temp=60C fan=2000rpm status=OK\n    [SYS] temp=85C fan=2500rpm status=WARN\n    [SYS] temp=99C fan=max status=WARN\n    [SYS] temp=-5C fan=1000rpm status=ERR\n    [SYS] temp=40C, fan=1100rpm status=OK\n    [SYS] temp=45C fan=1200rpm status=OK\n    [SYS] temp=30C fan=1000rpm status=OK\n    [SYS] temp=65C fan=1800rpm status=WARN\n    [SYS] temp=120C fan=0800rpm status=ERR\n    [SYS] temp=55C fan=1900rpm status=OK!\n    [SYS] temp=50C fan=1999rpm status=OK\n    [SYS] temp=51C fan=2000rpm status=OK\"\"\"\n\n    # regex matching start and end of string\n    pattern = re.compile(r\"\\[SYS\\] temp=(-?\\d{1,3})C(?:,)?\\s*fan=(\\d{1,4})rpm status=(OK|WARN|ERR)(?:!)?\", re.IGNORECASE)\n    total_severity = 0\n    for line in log_data.split('\\n'):\n        if not line:\n            continue\n        match = pattern.search(line)\n        if match:\n            temp = int(match.group(1))\n            fan = int(match.group(2))\n            status = match.group(3)\n\n            # Base severity calculation\n            if status == \"OK\":\n                total_severity += temp\n            elif status == \"WARN\":\n                total_severity += (temp * 2) + (fan // 100)\n            elif status == \"ERR\":\n                total_severity -= (fan // 10)\n\n            # Additional penalty condition\n            if temp > 50 and fan < 2000:\n                total_severity += 500\n    return total_severity\n\nprint(analyze_logs())\n```",
    "ground_truth": "2291",
    "source": "original_problems_4_10_26",
    "topic": "code_tracing"
  },
  {
    "problem_id": "op_prisoners",
    "problem_text": "20 prisoners are separated into individual cells. The cells are arranged in two lines of 10 cells which are separated by a hallway. This set up allows inmates to pass notes to their 2 neighboring cells (or 1 neighboring cell if the inmate is in an end cell) and to read notes from the 3 closest cells across the hallway (or the 2 closest cells if the inmate is in an end cell). Each inmate is uniquely assigned an ID number that happens to be prime. The warden jokingly tells them he'll release everyone if any inmate can tell him the product of every inmate's ID number, thinking that doing so would be impossible without a calculator and close communication. The desperate inmates try anyway, knowing that their math skills are flawless. Every hour, each inmate displays a number to their opposing cells and passes a note with that same number to their adjacent cells. They spend the rest of the hour calculating. How many iterations are required before an inmate can calculate the product that will get the warden to release everyone?",
    "ground_truth": "5",
    "source": "original_problems_4_10_26",
    "topic": "logic_puzzle"
  },
